name: hdc_perplexity_eval
version: "1.0.0"
language: zig
module: hdc_perplexity_eval

description: |
  HDC Perplexity Evaluation — Level 10A.1.2: Corpus-Level Model Quality Metric.
  Measures how well the HDC transformer predicts held-out text.

  === PERPLEXITY DEFINITION ===
  PPL = exp(-1/N * sum_{i=1}^{N} log P(token_i | context_i))

  In HDC:
    P(token | context) = softmax(similarity(output_hv, codebook_entry)) over all entries
    Where similarity = cosineSimilarity in [-1, 1], mapped to [0, 1] via (sim + 1) / 2

  Lower perplexity = better model. Random baseline for vocab V: PPL = V.

  === TERNARY SOFTMAX FOR PROBABILITY ===
  Standard: P(t) = exp(sim(t)/T) / sum_v exp(sim(v)/T)
  HDC alternative: P(t) = phi^(-rank(t)/T) / sum_k phi^(-k/T)
  Where rank(t) = position of token t when candidates sorted by similarity.
  This avoids float overflow and gives well-calibrated probabilities.

  === EVALUATION PROTOCOL ===
  1. Split corpus into train (80%), eval (10%), test (10%)
  2. Train HDC transformer on train set (no-backprop trainer)
  3. Evaluate perplexity on eval set (for hyperparameter tuning)
  4. Final perplexity on test set (reported metric)

  === CORPUS FORMATS ===
  Character-level: each character is a token (vocab ~95 printable ASCII)
  Word-level: each word is a token (vocab ~10k common words)
  Subword-level: BPE-like tokenization (vocab ~1k-5k)

  === TARGETS ===
  Random baseline (char-level, vocab=95): PPL = 95
  Decent model: PPL < 40
  Good model: PPL < 20
  State-of-art char-level: PPL < 5

  === LOSS CURVES ===
  Track per-epoch: train_loss, eval_loss, eval_perplexity
  Early stopping: if eval_loss increases for patience=3 epochs
  Convergence: eval_loss stabilizes within 1% for 2 epochs

  Trinity Identity: phi^2 + 1/phi^2 = 3
  Sacred Formula: V = n * 3^k * pi^m * phi^p * e^q

types:
  EvalConfig:
    fields:
      corpus_path: String
      train_split: Float
      eval_split: Float
      test_split: Float
      context_size: usize
      max_epochs: usize
      batch_size: usize
      patience: usize

  CorpusSplit:
    fields:
      train_samples: List<TrainSample>
      eval_samples: List<TrainSample>
      test_samples: List<TrainSample>
      vocab_size: usize
      total_tokens: u64

  PerplexityResult:
    fields:
      perplexity: Float
      avg_log_prob: Float
      num_tokens: usize
      num_correct_top1: usize
      accuracy_top1: Float
      accuracy_top5: Float

  LossCurvePoint:
    fields:
      epoch: usize
      train_loss: Float
      eval_loss: Float
      eval_perplexity: Float
      eval_accuracy: Float
      elapsed_ms: u64

  LossCurve:
    fields:
      points: List<LossCurvePoint>
      best_epoch: usize
      best_eval_ppl: Float
      converged: Bool
      converged_at_epoch: usize

  ComparisonEntry:
    fields:
      model_name: String
      version: String
      perplexity: Float
      accuracy: Float
      tokens_per_sec: Float
      memory_bytes: u64

  EvalReport:
    fields:
      config: EvalConfig
      corpus_stats: CorpusSplit
      loss_curve: LossCurve
      test_perplexity: PerplexityResult
      comparisons: List<ComparisonEntry>
      wall_time_sec: Float

  HDCPerplexityEval:
    fields:
      allocator: Allocator
      config: EvalConfig
      engine: HDCForwardEngine
      trainer: HDCTrainer
      corpus: CorpusSplit

behaviors:
  - name: initEval
    given: EvalConfig, HDCForwardEngine, HDCTrainer references
    when: Loads corpus, splits into train/eval/test
    then: Evaluation pipeline ready

  - name: loadCorpus
    given: Corpus path (text file)
    when: Reads text, tokenizes (char or word level), creates sliding window samples
    then: Returns CorpusSplit with train/eval/test partitions

  - name: tokenize
    given: Raw text string and tokenization mode (char, word, subword)
    when: Splits text into token sequence
    then: Returns list of token strings

  - name: createSamples
    given: Token sequence and context_size
    when: Creates sliding window (context[0..n-1], target[n]) pairs
    then: Returns list of TrainSample

  - name: computePerplexity
    given: List of TrainSamples and trained engine
    when: For each sample: forward, compute P(target|context) via phi-rank softmax
    then: Returns PerplexityResult with PPL, avg log prob, accuracies

  - name: computeTokenProbability
    given: Output hypervector, target token, codebook, temperature
    when: Ranks all codebook entries by similarity, assigns phi-rank weights
    then: Returns P(target) from the phi-rank distribution

  - name: trainAndEvaluate
    given: CorpusSplit and training config
    when: Trains epoch by epoch, evaluates after each, tracks loss curve
    then: Returns LossCurve with train/eval metrics per epoch

  - name: earlyStoppingCheck
    given: LossCurve and patience parameter
    when: Checks if eval_loss increased for patience consecutive epochs
    then: Returns whether to stop training

  - name: runFullEval
    given: EvalConfig
    when: Load corpus, train with early stopping, evaluate on test set
    then: Returns EvalReport with full loss curve and final perplexity

  - name: compareModels
    given: List of model configs to compare
    when: Runs evaluation for each, collects perplexity and throughput
    then: Returns comparison table as list of ComparisonEntry

  - name: generateReport
    given: EvalReport
    when: Formats as markdown table with loss curve, perplexity, comparisons
    then: Returns report string for documentation
